    <text>
        <body>
            <head>125. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                (<persName corresp="rec6rjfFsKmuW0bbp">Poindexter</persName>) to President <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reaga</persName>n<note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d125fn1">Source: <orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">National Security
                        Council</orgName>, National Security Council Institutional Files, Box SR
                    092, NSDD 206. Secret. Sent for action. Prepared by Wright. <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName> wrote his
                    initials in the upper right-hand corner of the memorandum.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1986-01-13">January 13, 1986</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>Instructions for Round IV—<rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Nuclear and Space Talks</rs> (<gloss target="#t_NST_1">NST</gloss>)</item>
            </list>
            <p>Our negotiators will be returning to Geneva this weekend to begin Round IV of the
                talks on January 16 covering <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_INF_1">INF</gloss> and Defense and Space. Recall that just before
                your summit and at the end of Round III, the U.S. provided a detailed
                counter-proposal involving the principle of <rs type="topic" corresp="recHoFOsQcM4e5M4k">50 percent reductions</rs>. The Soviet
                delegation has not had the chance to really address our proposals yet. Our task
                during this upcoming round will be to focus on the areas where we have the most
                common ground (<gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_INF_1">INF</gloss> reductions) and press the Soviets for an early, constructive
                response to our new proposals.</p>
            <p>With regard to Defense and Space we will concentrate on the offense/defense
                relationship and explain the nature of <gloss target="#t_SDI_1">
                    <rs type="program" corresp="recVUMTljdyxyuZz3">SDI</rs>
                </gloss> and your
                open laboratories initiative. The instructions to this delegation contain the main
                points which you have used personally with General Secretary <persName corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">Gorbachev</persName> on <gloss target="#t_SDI_1">
                    <rs type="program" corresp="recVUMTljdyxyuZz3">SDI</rs>
                </gloss>. These have been drawn from both the dialogue in Geneva and your
                subsequent letters and are provided for the delegations’ information at <hi rendition="simple_italic">Tab E</hi>.<note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d125fn2">Attached but not printed, at Tab E, are the draft <gloss target="#t_DST_1">DST</gloss> Instructions.</note>
            </p>
            <p>The <gloss target="#t_SACG_1">
                    <orgName corresp="recPNkfyWyGYfxAwz">SACG</orgName>
                </gloss> has met on the individual instruction
                cables at <hi rendition="simple_italic">Tabs B through E</hi>,<note n="3" place="foot" xml:id="d125fn3">Attached but not printed, at Tabs B, C, and D, are
                    draft <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                    </gloss>, <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss>, and <gloss target="#t_INF_1">INF</gloss>
                    Instructions.</note> and there are no outstanding issues. I believe it is
                appropriate for you to issue an NSDD (<hi rendition="simple_italic">Tab A</hi>)<note n="4" place="foot" xml:id="d125fn4">Printed below as <ref target="#d126">Document 126</ref>.</note> to further emphasize your involvement and
                desires for Round IV of the negotiations.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
            <table cols="3">
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">OK</hi>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">No</hi>
                    </cell>
                    <cell/>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell>That you sign the draft NSDD at <hi rendition="simple_italic">Tab A</hi>
                        approving the instructions for Round IV of the <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Nuclear and Space Talks</rs>.<note n="5" place="foot" xml:id="d125fn5">
                            <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName> initialed his
                            approval.</note>
                    </cell>
                </row>
            </table>
        </body>
    </text>
